50 // __cpp_exceptions is referred from
51 // https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/libstdc++/manual/using_exceptions.html
52 // gcc < 5 does not define __cpp_exceptions but __EXCEPTIONS,
53 // Microsoft C++ Compiler does not provide an option to disable exceptions
54 #ifndef DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
55 #if __cpp_exceptions || __EXCEPTIONS \
56  || (defined(_MSC_VER) && !defined(__clang__))
57 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 1
58 #else
59 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 0
60 #endif
61 #endif
62 
63 #if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
64 #define DNNL_TRAP() __builtin_trap()
65 #elif defined(__INTEL_COMPILER) || defined(_MSC_VER)
66 #define DNNL_TRAP() __debugbreak()
67 #else
68 #error "unknown compiler"
69 #endif
70 
71 #if DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
72 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) throw error(status, msg)
73 #else
74 #include <cstdio>
75 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) \
76  do { \
77  fputs(msg, stderr); \
78  DNNL_TRAP(); \
79  } while (0)
80 #endif

96 struct error : public std::exception {
97  dnnl_status_t status;
98  const char *message;
99 
104  error(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message)
105  : status(status), message(message) {}
106 
108  const char *what() const noexcept override { return message; }
109 
115  static void wrap_c_api(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message) {
116  if (status != dnnl_success) DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, message);
117  }
118 };
119 
121 template <typename T>
122 void validate_container_size(const T &v, const char *error_message,
123  int min_size = 1, int max_size = -1) {
124  const int size = (int)v.size();
125  if (size < min_size || (max_size >= 0 && size > max_size))
126  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments, error_message);
127 }
129 
131 template <typename T>
132 struct handle_traits {};
133 
147 template <typename T, typename traits = handle_traits<T>>
148 struct handle {
149 private:
150  static dnnl_status_t dummy_destructor(T) { return dnnl_success; }
151  std::shared_ptr<typename std::remove_pointer<T>::type> data_ {0};
152 
153 protected:
154  bool operator==(const T other) const { return other == data_.get(); }
155  bool operator!=(const T other) const { return !(*this == other); }
156 
157 public:
165  handle() = default;
166 
168  handle(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
170  handle<T, traits> &operator=(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
172  handle(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
174  handle<T, traits> &operator=(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
175 
181  explicit handle(T t, bool weak = false) { reset(t, weak); }
182 
188  void reset(T t, bool weak = false) {
189  data_.reset(t, weak ? &dummy_destructor : traits::destructor);
190  }
191 
197  T get(bool allow_empty = false) const {
198  T result = data_.get();
199  if (allow_empty == false && result == nullptr)
200  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(
201  dnnl_invalid_arguments, "object is not initialized");
202  return result;
203  }
204 
209  explicit operator T() const { return get(true); }
210 
214  explicit operator bool() const { return get(true) != nullptr; }
215 
222  bool operator==(const handle<T, traits> &other) const {
223  return other.data_.get() == data_.get();
224  }
225 
232  bool operator!=(const handle &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
233 };

401 dnnl::primitive::kind primitive::get_kind() const {
402  const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = get_primitive_desc();
403  // TODO (Roma): the code below is only needed because get_primitive_desc
404  // returns a C type.
405  dnnl_primitive_kind_t kind;
406  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
407  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&kind),
408  "could not get a primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
409  return static_cast<dnnl::primitive::kind>(kind);
410 }

666 #define DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(enum_name) \
667  inline enum_name operator|(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
668  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
669  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
670  } \
671 \
672  inline enum_name operator&(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
673  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
674  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
675  } \
676 \
677  inline enum_name operator^(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
678  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
679  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
680  } \
681 \
682  inline enum_name &operator|=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
683  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
684  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
685  return lhs; \
686  } \
687 \
688  inline enum_name &operator&=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
689  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
690  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
691  return lhs; \
692  } \
693 \
694  inline enum_name &operator^=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
695  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
696  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
697  return lhs; \
698  } \
699 \
700  inline enum_name operator~(enum_name rhs) { \
701  return static_cast<enum_name>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
702  }
703 
704 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(normalization_flags)
705 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(rnn_flags)

863 struct engine : public handle<dnnl_engine_t> {
864  friend struct primitive;
865  friend struct reorder;
866 
868  enum class kind {
870  any = dnnl_any_engine,
872  cpu = dnnl_cpu,
874  gpu = dnnl_gpu,
875  };
876 
877  using handle::handle;
878 
881  engine() = default;
882 
887  static size_t get_count(kind kind) {
888  return dnnl_engine_get_count(convert_to_c(kind));
889  }
890 
896  engine(kind kind, size_t index) {
897  dnnl_engine_t engine;
898  error::wrap_c_api(
899  dnnl_engine_create(&engine, convert_to_c(kind), index),
900  "could not create an engine");
901  reset(engine);
902  }
903 
904 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
905  engine(kind kind, cl_device_id device, cl_context context) {
912  dnnl_engine_t engine;
913  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_create_ocl(
914  &engine, convert_to_c(kind), device, context),
915  "could not create an engine");
916  reset(engine);
917  }
918 #endif
919 
920 #if DNNL_WITH_SYCL
921  DNNL_API engine(kind akind, const cl::sycl::device &dev,
927  const cl::sycl::context &ctx);
928 #endif
929 
934  engine(const handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t> &pd) {
935  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
936  error::wrap_c_api(
937  dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
938  dnnl::convert_to_c(dnnl::query::engine), 0, &c_engine),
939  "could not get an engine from a primitive_desc");
940  reset(c_engine, true);
941  }
942 
945  kind get_kind() const {
946  dnnl_engine_kind_t kind;
947  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_kind(get(), &kind),
948  "could not get kind of an engine");
949  return static_cast<engine::kind>(kind);
950  }
951 
952 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
953  cl_context get_ocl_context() const {
956  cl_context context = nullptr;
957  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_context(get(), &context),
958  "could not get an OpenCL context from an engine");
959  return context;
960  }
961 
964  cl_device_id get_ocl_device() const {
965  cl_device_id device = nullptr;
966  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_device(get(), &device),
967  "could not get an OpenCL device from an engine");
968  return device;
969  }
970 #endif
971 
972 #if DNNL_WITH_SYCL
973  cl::sycl::context DNNL_API get_sycl_context() const;
975 
977  cl::sycl::device DNNL_API get_sycl_device() const;
978 #endif
979 
985  template <typename primitive_desc>
986  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd) {
987  return query(pd, dnnl::query::engine);
988  }
989 
990 private:
991  static dnnl_engine_kind_t convert_to_c(kind kind) {
992  return static_cast<dnnl_engine_kind_t>(kind);
993  }
994 
995  template <typename primitive_desc>
996  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd, dnnl::query what) {
997  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
998  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
999  dnnl::convert_to_c(what), 0, &c_engine),
1000  "could not get an engine from a primitive_desc");
1001  return engine(c_engine, true);
1002  }
1003 };

1056 #if DNNL_CPU_THREADING_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_THREADPOOL
1057  void set_threadpool(threadpool_iface *threadpool) {
1065  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_attr_set_threadpool(get(), threadpool),
1066  "could not set stream threadpool attribute");
1067  }
1068 
1074  threadpool_iface *get_threadpool() {
1075  threadpool_iface *tp;
1076  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_attr_get_threadpool(get(), (void **)&tp),
1077  "could not set stream threadpool attribute");
1078  return tp;
1079  }
1080 #endif
1081 };

1084 struct stream : public handle<dnnl_stream_t> {
1085  using handle::handle;
1086 
1088  enum class flags : unsigned {
1091  default_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1093  in_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1095  out_of_order = dnnl_stream_out_of_order,
1097  default_flags = dnnl_stream_default_flags,
1098  };
1099 
1102  stream() = default;
1103 
1110  stream(const engine &engine, flags flags = flags::default_flags,
1111  const stream_attr &attr = stream_attr()) {
1112  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1113  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create_v2(&stream, engine.get(),
1114  static_cast<dnnl_stream_flags_t>(flags),
1115  attr.get(true)),
1116  "could not create a stream");
1117  reset(stream);
1118  }
1119 
1120 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1121  stream(const engine &engine, cl_command_queue queue) {
1126  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1127  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create_ocl(&stream, engine.get(), queue),
1128  "could not create a stream");
1129  reset(stream);
1130  }
1131 
1134  cl_command_queue get_ocl_command_queue() const {
1135  cl_command_queue queue = nullptr;
1136  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_get_ocl_command_queue(get(), &queue),
1137  "could not get an OpenCL command queue from a stream");
1138  return queue;
1139  }
1140 #endif
1141 
1142 #if DNNL_WITH_SYCL
1143  DNNL_API stream(const engine &eng, cl::sycl::queue &aqueue);
1148 
1150  cl::sycl::queue DNNL_API get_sycl_queue() const;
1151 #endif
1152 
1155  stream &wait() {
1156  error::wrap_c_api(
1157  dnnl_stream_wait(get()), "could not wait on a stream");
1158  return *this;
1159  }
1160 };

1812  struct desc {
1813  friend struct memory;
1815  dnnl_memory_desc_t data;
1816 
1819  desc() : data() {}
1820 
1836  desc(const memory::dims &dims, data_type data_type,
1837  format_tag format_tag, bool allow_empty = false)
1838  : data() {
1839  validate_dims(dims);
1840  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_tag(&data,
1841  (int)dims.size(), dims.data(), convert_to_c(data_type),
1842  convert_to_c(format_tag));
1843  if (!allow_empty)
1844  error::wrap_c_api(status,
1845  "could not construct a memory descriptor using a "
1846  "format tag");
1847  }
1848 
1864  desc(const memory::dims &dims, data_type data_type,
1865  const memory::dims &strides, bool allow_empty = false)
1866  : data() {
1867  validate_dims(dims);
1868  if (!strides.empty()) validate_dims(strides, (int)dims.size());
1869  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_strides(&data,
1870  (int)dims.size(), dims.data(), convert_to_c(data_type),
1871  strides.empty() ? nullptr : &strides[0]);
1872  if (!allow_empty)
1873  error::wrap_c_api(status,
1874  "could not construct a memory descriptor using "
1875  "strides");
1876  }
1877 
1881  desc(const dnnl_memory_desc_t &data) : data(data) {}
1882 
1885  //
1894  desc submemory_desc(const memory::dims &dims,
1895  const memory::dims &offsets, bool allow_empty = false) const {
1896  validate_dims(dims, data.ndims);
1897  validate_dims(offsets, data.ndims);
1898  dnnl_memory_desc_t sub_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
1899  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_submemory(
1900  &sub_md, &data, dims.data(), offsets.data());
1901  if (!allow_empty)
1902  error::wrap_c_api(status, "could not construct a sub-memory");
1903  return desc(sub_md);
1904  }
1905 
1950  desc reshape(const memory::dims &dims, bool allow_empty = false) const {
1951  if (data.ndims) validate_dims(dims, 1);
1952  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
1953  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_reshape(
1954  &out_md, &data, (int)dims.size(), dims.data());
1955  if (!allow_empty)
1956  error::wrap_c_api(
1957  status, "could not reshape a memory descriptor");
1958  return desc(out_md);
1959  }
1960 
1997  desc permute_axes(const std::vector<int> &permutation,
1998  bool allow_empty = false) const {
1999  validate_dims(permutation, data.ndims);
2000  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
2001  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_permute_axes(
2002  &out_md, &data, permutation.data());
2003  if (!allow_empty)
2004  error::wrap_c_api(status,
2005  "could not permute axes of a memory descriptor");
2006  return desc(out_md);
2007  }
2008 
2013  memory::dims dims() const {
2014  return memory::dims(data.dims, data.dims + data.ndims);
2015  }
2016 
2019  memory::data_type data_type() const {
2020  return static_cast<memory::data_type>(data.data_type);
2021  }
2022 
2027  size_t get_size() const { return dnnl_memory_desc_get_size(&data); }
2028 
2032  bool is_zero() const { return data.ndims == 0; }
2033 
2038  bool operator==(const desc &other) const {
2039  return dnnl_memory_desc_equal(&data, &other.data) != 0;
2040  }
2041 
2046  bool operator!=(const desc &other) const { return !operator==(other); }
2047  };

2258 #if DNNL_WITH_SYCL && defined(DNNL_USE_SYCL_BUFFERS)
2259  template <typename T, int ndims = 1>
2264  cl::sycl::buffer<T, ndims> get_sycl_buffer(size_t *offset = nullptr) const {
2265  static_assert(ndims == 1, "only 1D buffers supported");
2266 
2267  void *handle_ptr;
2268  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_get_data_handle(get(), &handle_ptr),
2269  "could not get SYCL buffer object");
2270 
2271  // XXX: workaround for ComputeCpp
2272  // ComputeCpp fails to construct zero-range buffer
2273  if (!handle_ptr)
2274  return cl::sycl::buffer<T, ndims>(cl::sycl::range<1>(1));
2275 
2276  auto &buf_u8 = *static_cast<cl::sycl::buffer<uint8_t, 1> *>(handle_ptr);
2277  if (offset) *offset = 0;
2278  auto range = cl::sycl::range<1>(buf_u8.get_size() / sizeof(T));
2279  return buf_u8.reinterpret<T, 1>(range);
2280  }
2281 
2287  template <typename T, int ndims>
2288  void set_sycl_buffer(cl::sycl::buffer<T, ndims> &buf) {
2289  auto range = cl::sycl::range<1>(buf.get_size());
2290  auto buf_u8 = buf.template reinterpret<uint8_t, 1>(range);
2291  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_set_data_handle(
2292  get(), static_cast<void *>(&buf_u8)),
2293  "could not set SYCL buffer object");
2294  }
2295 #endif

2302  }

2998  memory::desc query_md(query what, int idx = 0) const {
2999  std::vector<query> valid_q {query::src_md, query::diff_src_md,
3000  query::weights_md, query::diff_weights_md, query::dst_md,
3001  query::diff_dst_md, query::workspace_md, query::scratchpad_md,
3002  query::exec_arg_md};
3003  if (!std::any_of(valid_q.cbegin(), valid_q.cend(),
3004  [=](query q) { return what == q; }))
3005  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3006  "memory descriptor query is invalid");
3007 
3008  const dnnl_memory_desc_t *cdesc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query_md(
3009  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), idx);
3010  return cdesc ? memory::desc(*cdesc) : memory::desc();
3011  }

3157 protected:
3161  void reset_with_clone(const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd) {
3162  dnnl_primitive_desc_t new_pd;
3163  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_clone(&new_pd, pd),
3164  "could not clone a primitive descriptor");

3167 
3181  primitive_desc_base(
3182  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd, dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind)
3183  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind::undef) {}
3184 
3196  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
3197  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind)
3198  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, prop_kind, prop_kind) {}
3199 
3213  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
3214  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1,
3215  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2) {
3216  // It is OK to pass an empty primitive descriptor
3217  if (pd == nullptr) return;
3218 
3219  dnnl_status_t rc;
3220 
3221  dnnl_primitive_kind_t c_prim_kind = convert_to_c(prim_kind);
3222  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
3223  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
3224 
3225  // Check that primitive kind matches
3226  dnnl_primitive_kind_t pd_kind;
3227  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
3228  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_kind);
3229  error::wrap_c_api(
3230  rc, "could not get primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
3231  if (pd_kind != c_prim_kind)
3232  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3233  "primitive descriptor operation kind mismatch");
3234 
3235  // Check that propagation kind matches
3236  dnnl_prop_kind_t pd_prop_kind;
3237  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
3238  pd, dnnl_query_prop_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_prop_kind);
3239 
3240  // Something went wrong
3241  if (rc != dnnl_success && rc != dnnl_unimplemented)
3242  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3243  "could not get propagation kind from the primitive "
3244  "descriptor");
3245 
3246  // Everything is fine
3247  if ((rc == dnnl_unimplemented && c_prop_kind1 == dnnl_prop_kind_undef)
3248  || (rc == dnnl_success
3249  && (pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
3250  || pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind2))) {
3251  reset_with_clone(pd);
3252  return;
3253  }
3254 
3255  // We could get the propagation kind but there is a mismatch
3256  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3257  "primitive descriptor propagation kind mismatch");
3258  }
3259 
3260  using base = primitive_desc_base;
3261 };

3413 inline std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> convert_to_c(
3414  const std::vector<memory::desc> &mems) {
3415  std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> c_mems;

3419  return c_mems;

3628 struct primitive_desc : public primitive_desc_base {
3629  using primitive_desc_base::primitive_desc_base;
3630 
3631  primitive_desc() = default;
3632 
3655  primitive_desc(const_dnnl_op_desc_t desc, const primitive_attr *attr,
3656  const engine &engine, const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t hint_fwd_pd,
3657  bool allow_empty = false)
3658  : allow_empty_(allow_empty) {
3659  dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t iterator = nullptr;
3660  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_create(&iterator,
3661  desc, attr ? attr->get() : nullptr, engine.get(), hint_fwd_pd);
3662  if (!allow_empty)
3663  error::wrap_c_api(
3664  status, "could not create a primitive descriptor iterator");
3665  pd_iterator.reset(iterator);
3666  fetch_impl();
3667  }
3668 
3673  bool next_impl() {
3674  dnnl_status_t status
3675  = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_next(pd_iterator.get());
3676  if (status == dnnl_iterator_ends) return false;
3677  error::wrap_c_api(
3678  status, "could not advance a primitive descriptor iterator");
3679  fetch_impl();
3680  return true;
3681  }
3682 
3683 private:
3684  bool allow_empty_ = false;
3685  handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t> pd_iterator;
3686  void fetch_impl() {
3687  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_fetch(
3688  pd_iterator.get(allow_empty_));
3689  error::wrap_c_api(pd != nullptr || allow_empty_ ? dnnl_success
3690  : dnnl_runtime_error,
3691  "could not fetch a primitive descriptor from a primitive "
3692  "descriptor iterator");
3693  reset(pd);
3694  }
3695 };

5129  memory::validate_dims(padding_r, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
5130  error::wrap_c_api(
5131  dnnl_dilated_deconvolution_backward_weights_desc_init(&data,
5132  convert_to_c(algorithm), &src_desc.data,
5133  &diff_weights_desc.data, &diff_bias_desc.data,
5134  &diff_dst_desc.data, &strides[0], &dilates[0],
5135  &padding_l[0], &padding_r[0]),
5136  "could not create a descriptor for a dilated deconvolution "
5137  "weights gradient primitive");
5138  }
5139 
5173  desc(algorithm algorithm, const memory::desc &src_desc,
5174  const memory::desc &diff_weights_desc,
5175  const memory::desc &diff_dst_desc, const memory::dims &strides,
5176  const memory::dims &dilates, const memory::dims &padding_l,
5177  const memory::dims &padding_r) {
5178  memory::validate_dims(strides, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
5179  memory::validate_dims(dilates, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
5180  memory::validate_dims(padding_l, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
5181  memory::validate_dims(padding_r, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
5182  error::wrap_c_api(
5183  dnnl_dilated_deconvolution_backward_weights_desc_init(&data,
5184  convert_to_c(algorithm), &src_desc.data,
5185  &diff_weights_desc.data, nullptr,
5186  &diff_dst_desc.data, &strides[0], &dilates[0],
5187  &padding_l[0], &padding_r[0]),
5188  "could not create a descriptor for a dilated deconvolution "
5189  "weights gradient primitive");
5190  }

7742  // (Deliberately not using doxygen comments)
7743  //
7744  // Constructs an RNN primitive descriptor base from a C API primitive
7745  // descriptor while checking that it actually describes the expected
7746  // primitive by comparing propagation and primitive kinds. Caller can
7747  // pass two options propagation kinds. This is typically used to check
7748  // that propagation kind is inference or training forward propagation.
7749  //
7750  // @param pd C API primitive descriptor.
7751  // @param prop_kind1 Expected propagation kind.
7752  // @param prop_kind2 Expected propagation kind.
7753  // @param cell_kind Expected cell kind.
7754  rnn_primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
7755  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2,
7756  dnnl::algorithm cell_kind) {
7757  dnnl_rnn_desc_t *rnn_d;
7758  dnnl_status_t rc;
7759  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd, dnnl_query_rnn_d, 0, &rnn_d);
7760  error::wrap_c_api(rc,
7761  "could not retrieve a descriptor from a primitive descriptor "
7762  "for an RNN primitive");
7763 
7764  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
7765  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
7766  dnnl_alg_kind_t c_cell_kind = convert_to_c(cell_kind);
7767 
7768  bool ok = rnn_d->primitive_kind == dnnl_rnn
7769  && (rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
7770  || rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind2)
7771  && rnn_d->cell_kind == c_cell_kind;
7772 
7773  if (!ok)
7774  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
7775  "mismatch between expected and provided descriptors for an "
7776  "RNN primitive");
7777 
7778  reset_with_clone(pd);
7779  }
7780 };
7781

10455 struct resampling_forward : public primitive {
10457  struct desc {
10458  dnnl_resampling_desc_t data;
10459 
10481  desc(prop_kind prop_kind, algorithm algorithm,
10482  const memory::desc &src_desc, const memory::desc &dst_desc) {
10483  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_forward_desc_init(&data,
10484  dnnl::convert_to_c(prop_kind),
10485  convert_to_c(algorithm), nullptr,
10486  &src_desc.data, &dst_desc.data),
10487  "could not create a resampling forward descriptor");
10488  }
10489 
10504  desc(prop_kind prop_kind, algorithm algorithm,
10505  const std::vector<float> &factors,
10506  const memory::desc &src_desc) {
10507  memory::validate_dims(factors, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
10508  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_forward_desc_init(&data,
10509  dnnl::convert_to_c(prop_kind),
10510  convert_to_c(algorithm), &factors[0],
10511  &src_desc.data, nullptr),
10512  "could not create a resampling forward descriptor");
10513  }
10514 
10537  desc(prop_kind prop_kind, algorithm algorithm,
10538  const std::vector<float> &factors, const memory::desc &src_desc,
10539  const memory::desc &dst_desc) {
10540  if (!factors.empty())
10541  memory::validate_dims(factors, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
10542  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_forward_desc_init(&data,
10543  dnnl::convert_to_c(prop_kind),
10544  convert_to_c(algorithm), factors.data(),
10545  &src_desc.data, &dst_desc.data),
10546  "could not create a resampling forward descriptor");
10547  }
10548  };

10614 struct resampling_backward : public primitive {

10617  dnnl_resampling_desc_t data;
10618 
10633  desc(algorithm algorithm, const memory::desc &diff_src_desc,
10634  const memory::desc &diff_dst_desc) {

10639  }
10640 
10656  desc(algorithm algorithm, const std::vector<float> &factors,
10657  const memory::desc &diff_src_desc,
10658  const memory::desc &diff_dst_desc) {
10659  if (!factors.empty())
10660  memory::validate_dims(factors, diff_src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
10661  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_backward_desc_init(&data,
10662  convert_to_c(algorithm), factors.data(),
10663  &diff_src_desc.data, &diff_dst_desc.data),
10664  "could not create a resampling backward data descriptor");
10665  }

10930 inline void primitive::execute(const stream &stream,
10931  const std::unordered_map<int, memory> &args) const {
10932  std::vector<dnnl_exec_arg_t> c_args;
10933  c_args.reserve(args.size());
10934  for (const auto &a : args)
10935  c_args.push_back({a.first, a.second.get(true)});
10936 
10937  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_execute(get(), stream.get(),
10938  (int)c_args.size(), c_args.data()),
10939  "could not execute a primitive");
10940 }
